Frequently Asked Questions for Toll Brothers (NYSE:TOL)
What is Toll Brothers' stock symbol?

Toll Brothers trades on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) under the ticker symbol "TOL."



How often does Toll Brothers pay dividends? What is the dividend yield for Toll Brothers?

Toll Brothers declared a quarterly dividend on Tuesday, June 20th. Shareholders of record on Friday, July 14th will be paid a dividend of $0.08 per share on Friday, July 28th. This represents a $0.32 dividend on an annualized basis and a yield of 0.82%. The ex-dividend date is Wednesday, July 12th.  View Toll Brothers' Dividend History.



How were Toll Brothers' earnings last quarter?

Toll Brothers Inc. (NYSE:TOL) issued its quarterly earnings results on Tuesday, May, 23rd. The company reported $0.73 earnings per share for the quarter, topping the Thomson Reuters' consensus estimate of $0.63 by $0.10. The firm had revenue of $1.36 billion for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $1.26 billion. Toll Brothers had a net margin of 7.67% and a return on equity of 9.71%. The firm's revenue was up 22.2% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period in the prior year, the firm posted $0.51 EPS.  View Toll Brothers' Earnings History.



When will Toll Brothers make its next earnings announcement?

Toll Brothers is scheduled to release their next quarterly earnings announcement on Monday, August, 21st 2017. View Earnings Estimates for Toll Brothers.



Where is Toll Brothers' stock going? Where will Toll Brothers' stock price be in 2017?

15 analysts have issued 12 month price objectives for Toll Brothers' shares. Their predictions range from $29.00 to $46.00. On average, they expect Toll Brothers' share price to reach $39.27 in the next twelve months. View Analyst Ratings for Toll Brothers.



